					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10069175#post-4130434</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10069175/scp-4711#post-4130434</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 25 Jan 2019 13:58:12 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>ModernMajorGeneral</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>274283</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I kind of like this - as others said, it's relatable and has a certain charm - but I can't help but feel it's pretty bare. 'Hey isn't it funny when you go into the store and what you want isn't there' is a nice basis for a story but this is a very straightforward application of that. I don't think it necessarily needs deep and meaningful twists or extra fluff, but the test log was very much a 'what we said would happen in the description did, indeed, happen' sort of affair. Novote from me.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
